review_blob: Bomber to tulip glass. What it lacks in aroma it makes up in delicious raisin and caramel overtones. And perhaps a slight hint of molasses. If I could have this mouthfeel at all times, I would...so much balance and a glorious savory finish.

1qt bottle to pub glass. Like a fresh breakfast on a distant shore. Very heavy grapefruit with subtle honey and notes of molasses. Warm malty finish. As close to a perfect ale as I can remember. Tongue, prepare yourself.

Tap on location. What I imagine Greek ambrosia was supposed to smell like...sweet caramel and hint of grapefruit. Excellent taste, though perhaps a bit too bitter/dry on the after taste. Wholesome mouthfeel.

Nitro on location. Most wonderful smell of any coffee stout I have had. A little less malt or hop than I was expecting from a stout. Nitro makes it smooth, if a little watery. Great mouth watery aftertaste.
Slightly metallic aftertaste. Very smooth though, and a wonderful sourdough mouthfeel. Not as strong as a lot of Belgian style beers, but a good pair for many meals. Great golden shine.
